My husband and I are on lockdown at home in LA. Finally got to watch The Farewell tonight. It was tugging at my heart strings right from the start. The scene where you tell your mom how you felt about your grandpa just disappeared was the saddest 😭😭😭 The story brought back so many beautiful memories of my grandma in HK. Then suddenly she disappeared when we left for the US in the 70’s. I was devastated and confused as a 4 year old. Life as I knew it changed and has sort of etched a very deep scar in my mind. I absolutely loved the true happy ending! We don’t always see happy endings with cancer. One of my favorite movies! ❤️🙏🏻
